would be the case unless he had served<lb/>
his apprenticeship as well to the <hi xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                rend="underline">Art</hi>
            <lb/>
as to the <hi xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                rend="underline">Science</hi>. - But he would<lb/>
make a better farmer than a Man<lb/>
in other respects equal &amp; ignorant<lb/>
of Chemistry altogether; His Science<lb/>
as far as it went would be useful to<lb/>
him; But the discovery of principles<lb/>
&amp; the carrying them into execution require<lb/>
very different talents &amp; very different<lb/>
            <hi xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                rend="underline">habits</hi>.- The Constructor of the<lb/>
most accurate chart of latitudes<lb/>
&amp; longitudes would probably soon<lb/>
wreck a vessel if employed to steer<lb/>
it; but the practised Pilot may<lb/>
            <lb/>
            <pb xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                n="39"
                xml:id="pb-39"
                facs="#i39"/>
            <lb/>
37<lb/>
be securely directed by his labours. -<lb/>
- In proportion as Science advances<lb/>
all the practical methods become less<lb/>
complicated &amp; consequently more useful;<lb/>
- &amp; it is then principally that their<lb/>
application is made to the useful Arts.<lb/>
- The common labourer can never be en=<lb/>
=lightened by the general principles of<lb/>
philosophy - but He will employ<lb/>
any simple indication of the utility<lb/>
of which He is fully convinced. -<lb/>
- The <hi xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                rend="underline">great end</hi> of chemical investiga=<lb/>
=tion on this subject ought undoubtedly<lb/>
to be the discovery of <hi xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                rend="underline">practical methods</hi>. -<lb/>
but to this end Scientific principles,<lb/>
Theory &amp; experiment are alike necessary -<lb/>
The Mind ought to be constantly preserved<lb/>
in active speculation - &amp; Industry is<lb/>
never so efficacious as when assisted<lb/>
by Science - we may then apply to it<lb/>
the words of <rs xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                xml:id="ttag165"
                ref="#person_245"
                type="person">
               <name xml:id="tag165" type="person">
          Petronius
        </name>
            </rs> "Quicquid in<lb/>
            <lb/>
            <pb xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                n="40"
                xml:id="pb-40"
                facs="#i40"/>
            <lb/>
orbe vides paret mihi Florida<lb/>
            <rs xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                xml:id="ttag166"
                ref="#otherwork_087"
                type="otherwork">
               <bibl xml:id="tag166">
            Tellus cum volo, <hi rend="underline">fundit opes</hi>
               </bibl>
            </rs>"<lb/>
- It undoubtedly happens in agri=<lb/>
=cultural chemical experiments con=<lb/>
=ducted even after the most refined<lb/>
theoretical views that there are more<lb/>
than nine instances of failure for one of<lb/>
success; &amp; this is inevitable; from the<lb/>
Capricious &amp; uncertain nature of the<lb/>
causes that operate, &amp; from the impossi=<lb/>
=bility of calculating on all the circumstan=<lb/>
=ces that may interfere; - But this is<lb/>
far from proving the <hi xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                rend="underline">inutility</hi> of such<lb/>
trials - one happy result which can<lb/>
generally improve the methods of cultivation<lb/>
which can increase the general means<lb/>
of subsistence is worth the labour of<lb/>
a whole life; &amp; an unsuccessful<lb/>
experiment well observed must establish<lb/>
some truth or tend to remove some<lb/>
            <lb/>
            <pb xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                n="41"
                xml:id="pb-41"
                facs="#i41"/>
            <lb/>
39<lb/>
prejudice. -<lb/>
- Agricultural Chemistry is not<lb/>
in that state in which Natural Philoso=<lb/>
=phy seems to have been at the time of<lb/>
the foundation of the Royal Society when<lb/>
the Council recommended to their curator<lb/>
the celebrated <rs xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                xml:id="ttag167"
                ref="#person_246"
                type="person">
               <name xml:id="tag167" type="person">
          Rob<hi rend="superscript">t</hi>. Hooke
        </name>
            </rs> to make<lb/>
at least one capital discovery every<lb/>
week. -<lb/>
- It is only by much labour &amp; by<lb/>
multiplied trials conducted by many minds<lb/>
&amp; executed by many hands &amp; carried on<lb/>
through a long succession of years that<lb/>
any thing complete can be hoped for<lb/>
in this Branch of Knowledge. -<lb/>
- It has existed only for a <hi xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                rend="underline">few years</hi>;<lb/>
&amp; it aught not <hi xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                rend="underline">to be expected</hi> to be<lb/>
            <hi xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                rend="underline">perfect &amp; efficacious</hi> in its earliest<lb/>
            <hi xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                rend="underline">infancy</hi>; to be a giant at the moment<lb/>
of its birth. -<lb/>
            <lb/>
            <pb xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                n="42"
                xml:id="pb-42"
                facs="#i42"/>
            <lb/>
- A foundation has been laid &amp;<lb/>
if various labour &amp; ingenuity be<lb/>
