                n="68"
                xml:id="pb-68"
                facs="#i68"/>
            <lb/>
we might suppose it to be an elementary body<lb/>
&amp; this opinion was prevalent in all former<lb/>
times - Air was supposed to be undecom=<lb/>
=posable the most active &amp; pure of natural<lb/>
agents - by the lately discovered method<lb/>
of chemical Analysis we are however taught<lb/>
that it is compound in its essence &amp; that it<lb/>
contains many substances essentially different<lb/>
from each other. -<lb/>
