            <lb/>
of the rocky strata to the Soil." -<lb/>
- A Clayey subsoil will sometimes render a<lb/>
fertile or sandy <hi xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                rend="underline">Soil</hi> &amp; in this case it will<lb/>
retain moisture in such a manner as to be<lb/>
capable of supplying, that last by the earth<lb/>
above in consequence of the action of the<lb/>
dry atmosphere, upon it. -<lb/>
- A sandy or a gravelly subsoil often<lb/>
corrects the imperfections of too great a degree<lb/>
of tenacity &amp; absorbent power in the true soil. -<lb/>
- In calcareous Countries the Soil is often<lb/>
