be turned over &amp; fresh surfaces exposed to air<lb/>
&amp; the moment the smell becomes ammoniacal<lb/>
or putrid the materials should be used or<lb/>
spread out in smaller heaps - for if the<lb/>
process be carried on after this effect there is<lb/>
an immense loss of manure; &amp; the substance<lb/>
which at first was fluid &amp; an excellent<lb/>
